# Development tracker (`extension/docs/DEVELOPMENT_TRACKER.md`)

Single canonical plan for **done / doing / next / inbox**. Prose in that file is **English only** (repository Markdown policy).

## Read first

Treat **reading** `extension/docs/DEVELOPMENT_TRACKER.md` with the Read tool as **opening** it for this workflow.

**New machine / continuing work:**

1. Repo root **`AGENT_HANDOFF.md`**
2. **`extension/docs/BS2_PROTOCOL_INDEX.md`** (if task touches BS2 protocol)
3. **`extension/docs/DEVELOPMENT_TRACKER.md`**

**Before** substantial work on **`extension/`** when the task touches **features**, **BS2 protocol**, **Sensor Studio**, **Bitstream webview**, **bridge**, **dev scripts**, or the user mentions **roadmap**, **backlog**, **next steps**:

1. Read the tracker — **In progress**, **Planned / next**, **Incoming requirements**, **Parking lot**.
2. Align implementation wording with listed items when continuing existing work.

Skip a full read only for **narrow** fixes that do not affect planning.

## Update when something meaningful ships

- Add **`YYYY-MM-DD`** bullet under **Recently completed** in the tracker.
- Update **In progress** / **Planned / next** when priorities shift.
- Substantial session: row in **`AGENT_HANDOFF.md`** §7.

Do **not** log every trivial one-line change unless the user asks.

## Protocol changes

Follow **`.cursor/rules/bs2-protocol-change.mdc`** and skill **`bs2-protocol-change`**.

## Conflicts

**User chat instructions** override this rule for that task; still update tracker after shipped work or new requirements.

## Communication

**Always DO NOT respond in Chinese.** Use **English** and/or **Thai** only — **`communication-language.mdc`**.
